title: A real-time resource for Covid-19 news, advice, and commentary
body:
Some developing stories…
Case count: There are over 2.1 million confirmed cases in the U.S. and over 8.3 million confirmed cases worldwide. So far over 117,700 Americans have died from Covid-19. There are surely more.
Arizona and Texas will allow some local governments to require masks: The two states reversed course after mayors from several cities asked for the authority to require mask wearing.
A federal judge is ordering Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin to give Native American tribes their relief funds: The Trump Administration must distribute $679 million in emergency relief that the tribes should have received months ago.
